Hi @terrablue, thanks for the issue!

This rule has an option [`detectObjects`](https://eslint.org/docs/latest/rules/no-magic-numbers#detectobjects):

> A boolean to specify if we should detect numbers when setting object properties

Default is `false`:

```js
/* eslint no-magic-numbers: "error" */

class Foo {
  constructor() {
    this.baz = 2; // ok
  }
}

Foo.bar = 1; // ok

const obj = {
  foo: 3 // ok
}

```

I think the `detectObjects` option should also apply to class field initializers (perhaps we missed considering this rule in https://github.com/eslint/eslint/issues/14857), but would like more opinions on this.

